</h2>
<h3>
    Summer Steelhead vs. Winter Steelhead
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Summer Steelhead</strong>: Enter rivers as early as May and remain in freshwater until they spawn in winter. Often more active and aggressive in clear water.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Winter Steelhead</strong>: Begin entering rivers from November through March. These fish are typically larger and move in higher flows.
    </li>
</ul>
